MyBroadband is hosting its annual conference and expo at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand. The conference is the premier ICT event in South Africa and the meeting place for the country’s IT and telecoms community. South African speakers include MTN SA CEO Godfrey Motsa, Liquid Telecom CEO Reshaad Sha, former Telkom COO Brian Armstrong, SqwidNet MD Phathizwe Malinga, and Vodacom chief officer Jorge Mendes. The conference will also feature two international speakers – Bell Labs’ Fuad Siddiqui and Huawei Carrier Business Group’s Nigel Bruin. There will also be a panel discussion chaired by Jan Vermeulen, which will feature Supersonic MD Calvin Collett, Vodacom’s executive head for innovation Jannie van Zyl, and Huawei South Africa CTO Akhram Mohamed. For those who were unable to attend the 2019 conference, a live stream of the event is taking place. You can view the live stream on YouTube or Facebook – or watch in the embedded stream below: <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span> Read: 2019 FinTech Conference – Photos 